Former presidential candidates of the Young Progressives Party (YPP) and KOWA Party, Professors Kingsley Moghalu and Remi Sonaiya, are respectively billed to speak on good governance at this year’s edition of the Awujale and Paramount Ruler of Ijebuland, Oba Sikiru Adetona’s annual lecture. The third edition of Oba Sikiru Kayode Adetona Professorial Chair in Governance’s annual lecture series, has been scheduled for Thursday, next week, at Ijebu-Ode, Ogun State. The lecture, which holds in collaboration with the Olabisi Onabanjo University, Ago – Iwoye, will focus on good governance. The 2019 lecture has the theme: “Grassroots Governance: The Soft Underbelly of Nigeria’s Political Architecture.” It’s time to stop the killings, Awujale tells Buhari 2019 Presidency: Moghalu rejects Durotoye’s emergence as consensus candidate Moghalu asks Nigerians to hold NASS accountable